This paper is about neural architecture search (NAS), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a multi-objective genetic algorithm for NAS, which involves optimizing both the accuracy and computational complexity of neural networks. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimization and machine learning techniques, which are covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments in the paper are conducted on object classification and object alignment tasks, which are related to computer vision, covered by cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper proposes a population-based search algorithm, which involves optimization and control theory, covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control).
